messages.content: I'm good. Thanks. Glad to hear you are doing well. You are always welcome to come back when you are ready. It's really grown since you were here last. Consistently at 10-15 comics and about the same or more just in the audience. We are doing a few regular shows here now too.
Good. I'm teaching at Morton High School in Hammond. I keep on telling myself I should go to the open mike night, but I always feel lazy after work. How are you doing?
How's it going?
No. He enjoy having you whenever you can make it. Good luck in the new job & take care of the cousin.

I don't think I can make it tonight. I have to watch my little cousin. I really don't know if I'll be able to come much in June or July. But in August I start working in Hammond, so then it won't be so long of a drive
Cool. Looking forward to seeing you & introducing you to some of the other comics.
Thanks! I'll try to come this next Wednesday

It's up & down week to week but we are at it rain or shine packed or almost empty. We've had more comics new to the place the last weeks & will be getiing some improv the next few weeks. too because we are doing a improv show there July 1st & are using it for rehearsal . If you want to try improv the next ,month will be an especially good time to swing by but like always stand up is the still the main focus but all kinds of performers are welcome. Glad to hear you are well & congratulations on graduating!
Yeah. I ended up being really busy with work and school this last semester. But I just graduated, so I might be able to try some comedy again. How's the Wednesday open mic been going?
Hope all is well. Still interested in doing comedy?
I get it. Glad you are okay. & we are happy to have you  whenever you can
I'm good. I've just been busy with school, and it's kind-of a long drive for me to get out there. But I'll try to come this week. And I should make it more often come January
How's it going man? We miss you at the mic man.
https://www.facebook.com/events/1086531018101013/
No problem.
Sorry, I was out of town for my cousin's wedding. So I couldn't have come today anyway. And I don't know if I could have made all the other Sundays either. But thanks anyway

If you want to try improv I can get you into the class for free. Class is 4-5:30 next 6 sundays starting tommorow only thing thing you have to be able attend all 6 classes. If you on the fence here's  an oppurtunity to try it out .
'll definitely try to make it to the thing next Thursday
Thanks, man. Don't know if I'll do the improv class. I
http://disposabletheatreimprov.com/?page_id=65 If you want to take improv classes in Valpo here's some information. Same guy who taught me & my troupe.
